{"cursor":"1730","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{Infobox Software\n| name = Glow logo = developer = BBC latest release version = 1.7.7 latest\n| release date = operating system = Cross-platform (JavaScript) programming\n| language = JavaScript genre = JavaScript library license = Apache License\n| website = http://www.bbc.co.uk/glow/\n}} 'Glow' is an open-source JavaScript library created by the BBC. Development\non Glow began in 2007, {{cite web\n | url = http://www.bbc.co.uk/blogs/bbcinternet/2009/07/glow_javascript_library-\n | _open_s.html title = Glow JavaScript library open source release accessdate=2009-07-\n | 09}} and it was publicly released under an Apache License in July\n | 2009. {{cite web url = http://welcomebackstage.com/2009/07/public-unveiling-of-bbc-\n | glow/ title = Public unveiling of BBC glow accessdate=2009-07-09}}\n\nThe rationale for the development of the library, as opposed to using other\nlibraries such as JQuery or YUI, was to meet the BBC's stated targets for cross-\nbrowser compatibility (particulary Safari 1.3) {{cite web\n | url = http://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=693971 title = BBC Glow - Hacker\n | News }} that are of particular use in creating a website that uses data\n | that corresponds to times, for example broadcast metadata.\n","linknr":115,"url":"Glow_(JavaScript_library)","recorded":1375074563,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Glow_(JavaScript_library)&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Glow_(JavaScript_library)&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=ve